NODE_13_length_118614_cov_298.445574	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	47973	48476	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2724;product=tyrosine-type DNA invertase IpbA;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_001295805.1;translation=MSFPERNRCLIMMAFIHGFRASELLDLRLSDIDASGKQLNIRRIKNGFSTTHPLLPDEYNLIKLWLKQRKLIENGVEGDWLFLSRKRRPISRQHFFSIIREAGKRAGLAVKAHPHMLRHACGFALADNGVDTRLLQDYLGHRNIQHTVRYTASNAARFKGVWKKKPR;locus_tag=LOCUS_27130;gene=ipbA;note=WP_001295805.1 tyrosine-type DNA invertase IpbA (Enterobacteriaceae) [pid:100.0%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:89.3%25%2C Eval:1.5e-94],Domain:cl28330:XerC Integrase [Replication%2C recombination and repair%2C Mobilome: prophages%2C transposons]. The phage integrase family describes a number of recombinases with tyrosine active sites that transiently bind covalently to DNA. Many are associated with mobile DNA elements%2C including phage%2C transposons%2C and phase variation loci. This model represents XerD%2C one of two closely related chromosomal proteins along with XerC (TIGR02224). XerC and XerD are site-specific recombinases which help resolve chromosome dimers to monomers for cell division after DNA replication. In species with a large chromosome and with homologs of XerD on other replicons%2C the chomosomal copy was preferred for building this model. This model does not detect all XerD%2C as some apparent XerD examples score below the trusted and noise cutoff scores. XerC and XerD interact with cell division protein FtsK. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:6-167%2C Eval:7.1e-22%2C score:86.5%2C N-term missing],MGA_2724
