NODE_14_length_113170_cov_323.820289	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	73366	73659	.	-	0	ID=MGA_2853;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MSDEIYLTITGEQQGCISSRCGTSASIGNRWQIGHEDEIFAFSLSNSITNTGKGSQLHGLSFCKLIDKSSPLLINAINNNEQLFMEFDFYRINRFGR;locus_tag=LOCUS_28410;note=WP_001280050.1 type VI secretion system tube protein TssD (Escherichia coli) [pid:99.0%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:24.6%25%2C Eval:1.0e-50%2C partial hit],internal stop codon at [73366:73368](-),TIGR:TIGR03344%3B VI_effect_Hcp1: type VI secretion system effector%2C Hcp1 family [Name:TIGR03344%2C Eval:6.5e-28%2C score:95.7%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl01226:T6SS_HCP Type VI secretion system effector%2C Hcp. This family includes Hcp1 (hemolysin coregulated protein 1)%2C an exported%2C homohexameric ring-forming virulence protein from Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Hcp1 lacks a conventional signal sequence and is instead exported by means of the type VI secretion system%2C encoded by a pathogenicity cluster of a class previously designated IAHP (IcmF-associated homologous protein). Homologs of Hcp1%2C in this protein family%2C are found in various bacteria of which most but not all are known pathogens. Pathogens may have many multiple members of this family%2C with three to ten in Erwinia carotovora%2C Yersinia pestis%2C uropathogenic Escherichia coli%2C and the insect pathogen Photorhabdus luminescens. [Cellular processes%2C Pathogenesis] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-97%2C Eval:2.0e-30%2C score:102.8%2C C-term missing],MGA_2853
