NODE_40_length_30297_cov_310.704765	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	19366	22839	.	-	0	ID=MGA_4079;product=cellulose synthase complex outer membrane protein BcsC;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_001225074.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_40570;gene=bcsC;note=WP_001225074.1 cellulose synthase complex outer membrane protein BcsC (Escherichia coli) [pid:98.8%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:0.0e+00],Domain:cl26002:TPR_11 TPR repeat. The Tetratricopeptide repeat (TPR) typically contains 34 amino acids and is found in a variety of organisms including bacteria%2C cyanobacteria%2C yeast%2C fungi%2C plants%2C and humans. It is present in a variety of proteins including those involved in chaperone%2C cell-cycle%2C transcription%2C and protein transport complexes. The number of TPR motifs varies among proteins. Those containing 5-6 tandem repeats generate a right-handed helical structure with an amphipathic channel that is thought to accommodate an alpha-helix of a target protein. It has been proposed that TPR proteins preferentially interact with WD-40 repeat proteins%2C but in many instances several TPR-proteins seem to aggregate to multi-protein complexes. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:210-336%2C Eval:3.7e-10%2C score:59.0%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl27119:YbbN Negative regulator of GroEL%2C contains thioredoxin-like and TPR-like domains  [Posttranslational modification%2C protein turnover%2C chaperones]. This model represents eukaryotic protein disulfide isomerases retained in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and closely related forms. Some members have been assigned alternative or additional functions such as prolyl 4-hydroxylase and dolichyl-diphosphooligosaccharide-protein glycotransferase. Members of this family have at least two protein-disulfide domains%2C each similar to thioredoxin but with the redox-active disulfide in the motif PWCGHCK%2C and an ER retention signal at the extreme C-terminus (KDEL%2C HDEL%2C and similar motifs). [Superfamily%2C Aligned:618-732%2C Eval:1.1e-08%2C score:55.1%2C N-term missing],Domain:cl27017:YfgC Putative Zn-dependent protease%2C contains TPR repeats [General function prediction only].  [Superfamily%2C Aligned:253-499%2C Eval:4.2e-08%2C score:53.9%2C N-term missing],MGA_4079
